The paper discusses a technique for improving cellular network performance by mitigating inter-cell interference (ICI) through coordinated multi-point (CoMP) transmission. This topic falls under the area of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses stochastic geometry to analyze the coverage probability and spectral efficiency, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT), control systems (cs.SY), or multimedia (cs.MM) depending on the specific application.
